title: What to watch in the critical August jobs report - MarketWatch
text:
MARKETWATCH FRONT PAGE A rock-solid U.S. jobs report for August could go a long way in calming investors unnerved by global bloodbath in stock markets and a looming increase in U.S. interest rates. Here are five things to look to look for. See full story.
Five cars that make the Tesla Model X look like a deal Rolling your eyes at the price of a Tesla Model X? Wait till you see these. See full story.
‘Flintstone House’ on market for $4.2 million “The Flintstone House,” located in the upscale San Francisco suburb Hillsborough, Calif., is on the market for $4.2 million, according to San Francisco Realtor Judy Meuschke, who is listing the house. See full story.
Market timing model: Go 100% cash Mebane Faber’s market-timing model says to get out of the market completely. He may be right, says Brett Arends. But here’s why he’s not selling. See full story.
Sorry, Trump: Past businessmen did poorly as presidents History suggests that there is no link between success in the business world and success in the White House. In fact—and surprisingly—the opposite appears to be true See full story.
MARKETWATCH PERSONAL FINANCE China, where driving a Buick and drinking a PBR are signs you’ve made it. See full story.
